abstract: A prevailing sense among New Hampshire primary voters that Mitt Romney is the candidate most likely to defeat President Obama helped lift him to victory.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. -- A prevailing sense among New Hampshire primary voters that Mitt Romney is the candidate most likely to defeat Barack Obama helped lift him to victory on Tuesday.
